A Friday evening ghastly accident involving a commercial bus has left  commuters injured in Delta State. The crash occurred along Benin/Asaba highway by Umunede. Witnesses attributed the accident to overspeeding. The driver was said to have lost control of the bus and plunged into a drainage system. The bus, on its way from Asaba to Benin, reportedly somersaulted before crashing into the gutter. As of the time of the crash around 6:00 p.m, no life was reportedly lost, but the passengers sustained varying degrees of the injuries. It was gathered that officials of the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) with the assistance of sympathisers took the injured to nearby hospitals for medical attention. Details later… Jobs! Jobs!! Jobs!!!. Click on this link to register and get employed working and earning from home, we pay weekly directly to your designated bank account provided